<paragraph blockId="6.[128,768,795,2100]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">
D i s c u s s i o n. 
<bibRefCitation author="Brongniart, A." box="[355,566,795,819]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" pagination="203 - 240" refId="ref15150" refString="Brongniart, A. (1822 a): Sur la classification et la distribution des vegetaux fossiles en general, et sur ceux des terrains de sediment superieur en particulier. Introduction, Chapitre I. - Memoires du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle, 8: 203 - 240, pls 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1822">Brongniart (1822a)</bibRefCitation>
used this generic name for 
<taxonomicName authority="STERNBERG, 1820" authorityName="STERNBERG" authorityYear="1820" box="[237,767,827,851]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lepidodendraceae" genus="Lepidodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Lepidotae">
<emphasis box="[237,399,827,851]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Lepidodendron</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[467,574,827,851]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Lepidotae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sternberg, K. M. von" box="[584,767,827,851]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" refId="ref20641" refString="Sternberg, K. M. von (1820): Versuch einer geognostischbotanischen Darstellung der Flora der Vorwelt, Vol. I. 1. - in Commission im Deutschen Museum, F. Fleischer, Leipzig, 24 pp." type="book" year="1820">STERNBERG, 1820</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sternberg, K. M. von" box="[136,300,859,883]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" refId="ref20641" refString="Sternberg, K. M. von (1820): Versuch einer geognostischbotanischen Darstellung der Flora der Vorwelt, Vol. I. 1. - in Commission im Deutschen Museum, F. Fleischer, Leipzig, 24 pp." type="book" year="1820">Sternberg 1820</bibRefCitation>
had illegitimately referred to these sections as “tribes”). 
<bibRefCitation author="Brongniart, A." box="[278,491,891,915]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" pagination="203 - 240" refId="ref15150" refString="Brongniart, A. (1822 a): Sur la classification et la distribution des vegetaux fossiles en general, et sur ceux des terrains de sediment superieur en particulier. Introduction, Chapitre I. - Memoires du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle, 8: 203 - 240, pls 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1822">Brongniart (1822a)</bibRefCitation>
also included two new species within the genus: “ 
<taxonomicName authority="&quot; BRONGNIART, 1822 a" authorityName="&quot; BRONGNIART" authorityYear="1822" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiaceae" genus="Sagenaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coelata">
<emphasis box="[419,614,923,947]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Sagenaria coelata</emphasis>
” 
<bibRefCitation author="Brongniart, A." pageId="6" pageNumber="15" pagination="203 - 240" refId="ref15150" refString="Brongniart, A. (1822 a): Sur la classification et la distribution des vegetaux fossiles en general, et sur ceux des terrains de sediment superieur en particulier. Introduction, Chapitre I. - Memoires du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle, 8: 203 - 240, pls 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1822">BRONGNIART, 1822a</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and “ 
<taxonomicName authority="&quot; BRONGNIART, 1822 a" authorityName="&quot; BRONGNIART" authorityYear="1822" box="[285,764,955,979]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiaceae" genus="Sagenaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ophiurus">
<emphasis box="[285,510,955,979]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Sagenaria ophiurus</emphasis>
” 
<bibRefCitation author="Brongniart, A." box="[542,764,955,979]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" pagination="203 - 240" refId="ref15150" refString="Brongniart, A. (1822 a): Sur la classification et la distribution des vegetaux fossiles en general, et sur ceux des terrains de sediment superieur en particulier. Introduction, Chapitre I. - Memoires du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle, 8: 203 - 240, pls 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1822">BRONGNIART, 1822a</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, these latter two names were probably not validly published here as they were unaccompanied by diagnoses; an illustration with a close-up of the shoot was given for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="&quot; BRONGNIART" authorityYear="1822" box="[129,236,1083,1107]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiaceae" genus="Sagenaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coelata">
<emphasis box="[129,236,1083,1107]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">S. coelata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but this does not show the diagnostic characters sufficiently to count as an “illustration with analysis” to validate the species epithet under ICN, Art. 38.7–9. The only previous proposal to typify 
<taxonomicName box="[476,586,1180,1203]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiaceae" genus="Sagenaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[476,586,1180,1203]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Sagenaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was by 
<bibRefCitation author="Andrews, H. N." pageId="6" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 261" refId="ref14654" refString="Andrews, H. N. (1955): Index of generic names of fossil plants, 1820 - 1950. - US Geological Survey Bulletin, 1013: 1 - 261." type="journal article" year="1955">Andrews (1955)</bibRefCitation>
with “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="&quot; BRONGNIART" authorityYear="1822" box="[277,384,1211,1235]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiaceae" genus="Sagenaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coelata">
<emphasis box="[277,384,1211,1235]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">S. coelata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” but this has to be rejected as that species was not validly published in 1822. A 
<typeStatus box="[629,727,1243,1267]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">lectotype</typeStatus>
for 
<taxonomicName box="[129,239,1276,1299]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiaceae" genus="Sagenaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[129,239,1276,1299]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Sagenaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must therefore be selected from the species listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sternberg, K. M. von" box="[164,348,1307,1331]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" refId="ref20641" refString="Sternberg, K. M. von (1820): Versuch einer geognostischbotanischen Darstellung der Flora der Vorwelt, Vol. I. 1. - in Commission im Deutschen Museum, F. Fleischer, Leipzig, 24 pp." type="book" year="1820">Sternberg (1820)</bibRefCitation>
under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="STERNBERG" authorityYear="1820" box="[426,761,1307,1331]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lepidodendraceae" genus="Lepidodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Lepidotae">
<emphasis box="[426,588,1307,1331]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Lepidodendron</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[654,761,1307,1331]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Lepidotae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as Brongniart was clearly (albeit indirectly) including them within the genus (ICN, Arts 10.2, 10.3). In order to simplify the situation, we designate here 
<taxonomicName authority="STERNBERG, 1820" authorityName="STERNBERG" authorityYear="1820" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lepidodendraceae" genus="Lepidodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aculeatum">
<emphasis box="[485,767,1403,1427]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Lepidodendron aculeatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sternberg, K. M. von" box="[129,307,1436,1460]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" refId="ref20641" refString="Sternberg, K. M. von (1820): Versuch einer geognostischbotanischen Darstellung der Flora der Vorwelt, Vol. I. 1. - in Commission im Deutschen Museum, F. Fleischer, Leipzig, 24 pp." type="book" year="1820">STERNBERG, 1820</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<typeStatus box="[340,438,1435,1459]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[471,581,1436,1459]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiaceae" genus="Sagenaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[471,581,1436,1459]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Sagenaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– it is conspecific with one of the specimens illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Brongniart, A." box="[563,764,1467,1492]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" pagination="203 - 240" refId="ref15150" refString="Brongniart, A. (1822 a): Sur la classification et la distribution des vegetaux fossiles en general, et sur ceux des terrains de sediment superieur en particulier. Introduction, Chapitre I. - Memoires du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle, 8: 203 - 240, pls 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1822">Brongniart (1822a</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 12, fig, 6 ‒ as “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="&quot; BRONGNIART" authorityYear="1822" box="[325,429,1499,1523]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lycopodiaceae" genus="Sagenaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lycopodiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coelata">
<emphasis box="[325,429,1499,1523]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">S. coelata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[128,768,795,2100]" lastBlockId="6.[843,1482,151,760]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[304,466,1531,1555]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lepidodendraceae" genus="Lepidodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[304,466,1531,1555]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Lepidodendron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally based on external morphological characters of the stem as seen in adpressions and casts. However, subsequent work on coal ball specimens has resulted in the stems being subdivided into a number of other fossil-genera based on anatomical features, including 
<taxonomicName authority="DIMICHELE, 1985" authorityName="DIMICHELE" authorityYear="1985" box="[357,763,1691,1715]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Diaphorodendraceae" genus="Diaphorodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[357,548,1691,1715]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Diaphorodendron</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="DiMichele, W. A." box="[567,763,1691,1715]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" pagination="453 - 458" refId="ref17245" refString="DiMichele, W. A. (1985): Diaphorodenron gen. nov. a segregate from Lepidodendron (Pennsylvannian Age). - Systematic Botany, 10: 453 - 458. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2419138" type="journal article" year="1985">DIMICHELE, 1985</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="DIMICHELE et BATEMAN, 1992" authorityName="DIMICHELE et BATEMAN" authorityYear="1992" box="[128,700,1724,1748]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Diaphorodendraceae" genus="Synchysidendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[128,309,1724,1748]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Synchysidendron</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="DiMichele, W. A. &amp; Bateman, R. M." box="[334,700,1724,1748]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" pagination="605 - 617" refId="ref17289" refString="DiMichele, W. A., Bateman, R. M. (1992): Diaphorodendraceae, fam. nov. (Lycopsida: Carboniferous): systematics and evolutionary relationships of Diaphorodendron and Synchysidendron, gen. nov. - American Journal of Botany, 79: 605 - 617. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / j. 1537 - 2197.1992. tb 14602. x" type="journal article" year="1992">DIMICHELE et BATEMAN, 1992</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="BATEMAN et DIMICHELE, 1991" authorityName="BATEMAN et DIMICHELE" authorityYear="1991" box="[129,651,1756,1780]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lepidodendraceae" genus="Hizemodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[129,298,1756,1780]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Hizemodendron</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bateman, R. M. &amp; DiMichele, W. A." box="[313,651,1756,1780]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" pagination="195 - 205" refId="ref14939" refString="Bateman, R. M., DiMichele, W. A. (1991): Hizemodendron, gen. nov., a pseudoherbaceous segregate of Lepidodendron (Pennsylvanian): Phylogenetic context for evolutionary changes in lycopsid growth and architecture. - Systematic Botany, 16: 195 - 205. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2418983" type="journal article" year="1991">BATEMAN et DIMICHELE, 1991</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. A fourth fossil-genus was recognised on anatomical characteristics in coal ball fossils, based round the species 
<taxonomicName authority="WATSON, 1907" authorityName="WATSON" authorityYear="1907" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lepidodendraceae" genus="Lepidodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hickii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Lepidodendron hickii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Watson, D. M. S." box="[195,351,1852,1876]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" refId="ref21357" refString="Watson, D. M. S. (1907): On a confusion of two species (Lepidodendron Harcourtii Witham and L. Hickii sp. nov.) under L. Harcourtii Witham in Williamson's XIX Memoir; with a description of L. Hickii sp. nov. - Memoirs and Proceedings of the Manchester Literary and Philosophical Society, 51 (3, 13): 22 pp." type="book" year="1907">WATSON, 1907</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="DiMichele, W. A." box="[362,555,1852,1876]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" pagination="317 - 333" refId="ref17205" refString="DiMichele, W. A. (1983): Lepidodendron hickii and generic delimitation in Carboniferous lepidodendrid lycopods. - Systematic Botany, 8: 317 - 333. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2418485" type="journal article" year="1983">DiMichele (1983)</bibRefCitation>
stated that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="WATSON" authorityYear="1907" box="[679,767,1852,1876]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lepidodendraceae" genus="Lepidodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hickii">
<emphasis box="[679,767,1852,1876]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">L. hickii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has deep ligule pits and infrafoliar parichnos, with the larger cushions having a relatively broad lower surface and a low keel with plications, and is very similar to the leaf cushions of the 
<typeStatus box="[194,240,1980,2004]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName box="[356,518,1980,2004]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lepidodendraceae" genus="Lepidodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[356,518,1980,2004]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Lepidodendron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the adpression species 
<taxonomicName box="[128,271,2012,2036]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lepidodendraceae" genus="Lepidodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aculeatum">
<emphasis box="[128,143,2012,2035]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[160,271,2012,2036]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">aculeatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Bateman, R. M. &amp; DiMichele, W. A." box="[297,705,2011,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" pagination="195 - 205" refId="ref14939" refString="Bateman, R. M., DiMichele, W. A. (1991): Hizemodendron, gen. nov., a pseudoherbaceous segregate of Lepidodendron (Pennsylvanian): Phylogenetic context for evolutionary changes in lycopsid growth and architecture. - Systematic Botany, 16: 195 - 205. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2418983" type="journal article" year="1991">Bateman and DiMichele (1991: 195)</bibRefCitation>
went further and stated that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="WATSON" authorityYear="1907" box="[365,452,2044,2068]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lepidodendraceae" genus="Lepidodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hickii">
<emphasis box="[365,380,2044,2067]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[393,452,2044,2068]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">hickii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the anatomically preserved equivalent of 
<taxonomicName box="[277,418,2076,2100]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lepidodendraceae" genus="Lepidodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aculeatum">
<emphasis box="[277,292,2076,2099]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[307,418,2076,2100]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">aculeatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and as a consequence, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="WATSON" authorityYear="1907" box="[679,767,2076,2100]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lepidodendraceae" genus="Lepidodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hickii">
<emphasis box="[679,767,2076,2100]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">L. hickii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would have to be regarded as a later heterotypic synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[843,982,184,208]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lepidodendraceae" genus="Lepidodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aculeatum">
<emphasis box="[843,982,184,208]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">L. aculeatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and so supressed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[843,1482,151,760]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">
This more refined generic classification undoubtedly provides a better systematic resolution of the anatomically preserved fossils but there are problems when trying to use it with the more commonly found adpressions and casts of the stems. One of the characters used for distinguishing these fossil-genera (the presence or absence of infrafoliar parichnos) can sometimes be recognised in adpressions and casts, but relying entirely on just this one feature as a diagnostic feature may give a false impression of certainty with such fossils and make comparisons much more difficult (
<bibRefCitation author="Laveine, J. - P. &amp; Zhang, S. Z. &amp; Liu, L. J. &amp; Gu, F. B. &amp; Liu, Y. A. &amp; Wen, J. G. &amp; Lemoigne, Y." box="[942,1154,541,565]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" pagination="567 - 651" refId="ref19065" refString="Laveine, J. - P., Zhang, S. Z., Liu, L. J., Gu, F. B., Liu, Y. A., Wen, J. G., Lemoigne, Y. (2003): The Late Carboniferous floras of the Delingha area (Wulan County, Qinghai Province, Northwest China). - Revue de Paleobiologie, 22: 567 - 651." type="journal article" year="2003">Laveine et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
). In our view, a better solution is to have separate taxonomies for the adpressions / casts and for the anatomically preserved fossils. Since the 
<typeStatus box="[1436,1482,606,630]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[874,1036,638,662]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lepidodendraceae" genus="Lepidodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[874,1036,638,662]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Lepidodendron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an adpression, that name should only be used for such fossils, and an alternative generic name is needed for the group of anatomically-preserved species centred on “ 
<taxonomicName box="[973,1135,736,760]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lepidodendraceae" genus="Lepidodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[973,1135,736,760]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Lepidodendron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” 
<taxonomicName authorityName="WATSON" authorityYear="1907" box="[1154,1213,736,760]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Lepidodendraceae" genus="Lepidodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidodendrales" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hickii">
<emphasis box="[1154,1213,736,760]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">hickii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
